8.11.20  4:44 am   How do I draw faces? Or actually let me rephrase that. How do I give souls to the expressions of the characters I've created? I find it easy enough to draw the rest of the body as body language doesn't need as much careful consideration, but faces really make me struggle as even the slightest detail changes the observed expression drastically. All of my characters look like they've had their soul vacuumed out by the ghost-busters leaving their faces stiff and without emotion. I've tried a lot of things but none of the satanic rituals worked. So tell me, which ritual did you use to imbue souls into your music without attracting any evil spirits or accidentally haunting the music???

8.10.20  10:03 pm   i've seen you say that you don't collaborate well with people and i think i am the same way in that i tend to tell the people im trying to play with things they are playing wrong like chord voicings and feel on drums and things. this time alone has been a really great learning time for me because i dont have to really worry about that currently. when i inevitably start playing with people more i think my perfectionism will be worse than ever though. when you play music with people how do you stop yourself from being annoying like me?

      (i really try hard not to, and its coming from a good place, but i end up being annoying to rehearse with) also, ive been learning a lot from learning lots of your short songs and im really falling in love more with the keyboard. thank you for your amazing music!
